"'''Vandaag'''" is a song by Dutch producer [[Bakermat]]. It was released in August 2012 as a single and reached the top ten in [[Austria]], [[Belgium]],<ref name="lescharts.com">{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://lescharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Bakermat&titel=Vandaag&cat=s |title=Bakermat - Vandaag |publisher=lescharts.com |date= |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Bakermat&titel=Vandaag&cat=s |title=Bakermat - Vandaag |publisher=ultratop.be |date= |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref> [[France]],<ref name="lescharts.com"/> and the [[Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Bakermat&titel=Vandaag&cat=s |title=Bakermat - Vandaag |publisher=dutchcharts.nl |date= |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref>

It was re-released by Sony in 2014 as "'''One Day (Vandaag)'''" becoming a hit in several European countries.

==Content==
The song consists of an integrated sample of the "[[I Have a Dream]]" speech by [[Martin Luther King, Jr.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yzCWGGG2gQc |title=Bakermat - Vandaag (Original Mix) |publisher=YouTube |date=2012-08-30 |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref>

